25#pragma once
26
27#include "CachedResourceClient.h"
28#include <wtf/HashCountedSet.h>
29#include <wtf/Vector.h>
30
31namespace WebCore {
32
33// Call this "walker" instead of iterator so people won't expect Qt or STL-style iterator interface.
34// Just keep calling next() on this. It's safe from deletions of items.
35template<typename T>
36class CachedResourceClientWalker {
37public:
38 CachedResourceClientWalker(const HashCountedSet<CachedResourceClient*>& clientSet)
39 : m_clientSet(clientSet)
40 , m_clientVector(clientSet.size())
41 {
42 size_t clientIndex = 0;
43 for (const auto& client : clientSet)
44 m_clientVector[clientIndex++] = client.key;
45 }
46
47 T* next()
48 {
49 size_t size = m_clientVector.size();
50 while (m_index < size) {
51 CachedResourceClient* next = m_clientVector[m_index++];
52 if (m_clientSet.contains(next)) {
53 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(T::expectedType() == CachedResourceClient::expectedType() || next->resourceClientType() == T::expectedType());
54 return static_cast<T*>(next);
55 }
56 }
57 return nullptr;
58 }
59private:
60 const HashCountedSet<CachedResourceClient*>& m_clientSet;
61 Vector<CachedResourceClient*> m_clientVector;
62 size_t m_index { 0 };
63};
64
65} // namespace WebCore
